# QUICK START FOR LOCAL DEPLOYMENT
# This project requires a PostgreSQL database

# OPTION 1: Use Railway.app (Recommended - Free tier available)
# 1. Go to https://railway.app
# 2. Click "Deploy Now" or create an account
# 3. Add PostgreSQL plugin from the marketplace
# 4. Copy the DATABASE_URL from the PostgreSQL plugin connection settings
# 5. Paste it below:
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@db.penfzkpvbhpdewzgcidt.supabase.co:5432/postgres

# OPTION 2: Use Supabase.com (Free tier: 500MB storage)
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com and sign up
# 2. Create a new project
# 3. Go to Settings > Database and copy the "URI" connection string
# 4. Paste it below (format: postgresql://postgres:password@host:5432/postgres):
# DATABASE_URL=

# OPTION 3: Local PostgreSQL (requires PostgreSQL installed on your machine)
# 1. Install PostgreSQL from https://www.postgresql.org/download/windows/
# 2. Start PostgreSQL service
# 3. Create a database and user, then use the connection string below:
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/profile

# OPTION 4: Docker PostgreSQL (requires Docker Desktop running)
# 1. Make sure Docker Desktop is started
# 2. Run: docker run --name postgres-local -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=password -p 5432:5432 -d postgres:latest
# 3. Use: DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/postgres

# After setting DATABASE_URL, run: npm run dev
